Germany postpones the launch of a new battleship
The latest frigate of the German fleet had to be put into operation in 2014 in order to replace the aged warships of the Cold War, but this will not be implemented until at least next year due to the faulty systems and the head-to-head growing costs, local media reported.
The introduction into operation of ‘Rheinland-Pfalz’, the leading brand ship of new frigates of the Baden-Wuertemberg class, was postponed until the first half of 2019, according to the Die Zeit newspaper, which quoted the military spokesman as saying.
